Text.Value: Leave.
No. Bigger. Angrier.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lights flicker above the Elder Rothe

Text.Value: Do not think on it further. Rest. I will see you safe.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lights flashing above both rothe
EditorData.NodeContext: Trying to be comforting. Not doing a great job,

Text.Value: Tell me what you can about Ketheric Thorm.
*The lights must mean something, but you can't interpret the flashes.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lights flicker above both rothe

Text.Value: *That fear runs deep, stretching back across generations.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lights flicker above both rothe

Text.Value: *One beast notices you and dulls his lights, ending the conversation.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Elder Rothe dulls his lights

Text.Value: Do you mean Ketheric Thorm, the Dark Justiciar commander?

EditorData.logicalname: Know of Ketheric only through Halsin

Text.Value: *Ketheric Thorm - an inescapable name. His legacy has shadowed the region, above ground and under.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lights flicker above the Elder Rothe

Text.Value: Leave.
Mm. Mighty elf, cloaked in darkness. Ten masters ago, and ten more. But I remember.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lights flicker above the Elder Rothe

Text.Value: *The beast flashes a message of comfort. But his eyes betray his concern.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lights flicker above both rothe

Text.Value: That was a long time ago. What does Nere have to do with Ketheric?
*The name means little to you, yet your heart pulses to its rhythm. Thorm. Thorm.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lights flicker above the Elder Rothe

Text.Value: *The Absolute's Chosen, Ketheric Thorm. So vast is his repute that even the beasts bellow his name.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lights flicker above the Elder Rothe
EditorData.logicalname: Nere told you Ketheric is chosen

Text.Value: *The beasts continue their discussion, lights flickering above them.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lights flicker above both rothe

Text.Value: There was the work, and the blood. There was the Thorm's army. There was the hellbeast that broke them.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lights flicker above the Elder Rothe

Text.Value: What kind of hellbeast could have destroyed Ketheric's army?
Afraid. Afraid of Thorm.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lights flashing above both rothe.

Text.Value: Leave.
*One of the beasts seems exhausted. His lights flash in slow, methodical beats.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The Deep Rothe Calf's lights flash slowly

Text.Value: Pay attention to the lights.
Blessed to see many live. Cursed to see many die.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lights flicker above the Elder Rothe

Text.Value: *The roth grunt softly at each other. Small lights flash about their heads in quick, erratic patterns.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Small lights flashing above rothe heads

Text.Value: Still your body and quietly observe.
What are you doing?
You're not the only one who fears Ketheric Thorm. What do you know of him?
I know not so I say not. Yet I hear his name again, said by the shadows.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lights flicker above the Elder Rothe

Text.Value: Ketheric Thorm's influence stretches far. What was he doing down here?
Pay attention to the lights.
*You discern subtle emotions in the lights' patterns. There is pain, sadness - and fear.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lights flicker above both rothe

Text.Value: Impressive memory. How old are you exactly?
Simply watch the roth.
I outlived my mother, and her mother's mother, and many mothers beyond.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lights flicker above the Elder Rothe

Text.Value: Tired. Sleep.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lights flicker above both rothe

Text.Value: *Ketheric Thorm, the Absolute's Chosen. Even in these depths, he has left his vicious mark.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lights flicker above the Elder Rothe

Text.Value: Hellbeast? You mean like me? Horns?
The Ketheric Thorm's name faded into stone. Until the Nere came.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lights flicker above the Elder Rothe

Text.Value: You honour me with your ancient wisdom.
I saw tusks and flesh, smelled fire and eggs. It came with the mask-men - crashing and smashing.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lights flicker above the Elder Rothe

Text.Value: *Ketheric Thorm - a familiar name. Halsin mentioned his stronghold deep underground.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lights flicker above the Elder Rothe
EditorData.logicalname: Knows of Ketheric through Halsin/hasn't seen Ketheric or Jaheira

Text.Value: *The two roth moan quietly as lights flash about their heads.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: *The two Roth paw the ground in irritatio'
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: *The two Roth paw the ground in irritation as lights flash about their heads.*

Text.Value: You fear this Ketheric Thorm. Who is he?

EditorData.logicalname: Never heard of Ketheric from Jaheira Halsin or Moonrise

Text.Value: I heard his name whispered. The rock shivers from the sound. The Ketheric Thorm.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lights flicker above the Elder Rothe
EditorData.NodeContext: Increasingly insistent but not too loud or angry.

Text.Value: *The beast sternly ignores you.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: Rothe eating their food. Ignoring the player
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: <placeholder>

Text.Value: Rest, little one. But do not take long - I feel his shadow.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lights flicker above the Elder Rothe
EditorData.NodeContext: Stern but trying not to be too cruel

Text.Value: *You recognise the spell - Dancing Lights. It is how roth communicate with each other.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lights flicker above both rothe

Synopsis:
This occurs between two Rothe. The first is a younger Rothe who desires  freedom and a life without pain. The other Rothe is older and more stern. He has worked since the times of Ketheric.


Player can speak with them or listen in on their conversation with an animal handling check.
